---
import ServicePage from '../layouts/ServicePage.astro';
import ContactForm from '../components/ContactForm.astro';
---

<ServicePage
  title="Keyword Research Services UK | MM SEO"
  description="Strategic keyword research from an 18-year SEO consultant. Uncover high-value search terms that drive qualified traffic to your site. Manchester & UK-based."
  canonical="https://www.mmseo.co.uk/keyword-research/"
  breadcrumb="Keyword Research"
>

  <!-- ── 1. Hero band (dark) ─────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-hero section-dark">
    <div class="container sp-hero-inner reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Keyword Research | Manchester &amp; UK</p>
      <h1 class="sp-h1">Keyword Research That Drives Revenue, Not Just Traffic</h1>
      <p class="sp-intro">
        Most keyword research produces a long list of terms nobody converts on. I build
        keyword strategies around what your customers actually search, matched to
        commercial intent, mapped to your site architecture, and prioritised by
        realistic opportunity.
      </p>
      <a href="/#contact" class="btn-primary">Book a Free Consultation</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 2. Main content (light) ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-content section-light">
    <div class="container sp-content-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2">Keyword Research vs Keyword Guessing</h2>

      <p>
        There's a world of difference between picking keywords based on instinct and
        building a strategy grounded in data. I use a combination of tools: Ahrefs,
        Google Search Console, Google Keyword Planner, and competitor analysis, to
        build a complete picture of the search landscape around your business.
      </p>
      <p>
        The goal isn't maximum search volume. It's finding the terms where the intent
        matches your offer, the competition is beatable within your budget and timeline,
        and ranking will produce actual enquiries or sales, not just impressions.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every keyword recommendation I make is tied to a rationale. You'll understand
        why each term is on the list and what winning it means commercially.
      </p>

      <h3 class="sp-h3">What's included</h3>
      <ul class="sp-list">
        <li><strong>Search intent mapping</strong>: categorising keywords by informational, navigational, commercial, and transactional intent</li>
        <li><strong>Competitor gap analysis</strong>: identifying terms your competitors rank for that you don't, and assessing the opportunity</li>
        <li><strong>Head term vs long-tail strategy</strong>: balancing high-volume targets with the easier wins that drive early momentum</li>
        <li><strong>Content architecture mapping</strong>: assigning keywords to existing or new pages to avoid internal cannibalisation</li>
        <li><strong>Localised keyword sets</strong>: geo-specific terms for Manchester, Stockport, and your key target locations</li>
        <li><strong>Seasonality analysis</strong>: identifying demand patterns that should shape content and campaign timing</li>
        <li><strong>Priority scoring</strong>: each keyword ranked by a combination of volume, difficulty, intent match, and commercial value</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 3. Why it matters (dark) ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-why section-dark">
    <div class="container sp-why-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="sp-h2 chalk">The Foundation of Every Campaign</h2>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        Keyword research isn't a one-time deliverable that sits in a spreadsheet. It's
        the strategic layer that shapes everything: which pages you build, what content
        you write, how your site is structured, and where you focus link acquisition.
        Done properly, it gives you a clear map from your current position to where you
        want to be.
      </p>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        I also use keyword research to identify content gaps: topics your customers are
        searching for where you have no presence. These gaps represent some of the
        highest-value opportunities, especially in competitive markets where going
        head-to-head on core terms isn't the right first move.
      </p>
      <p class="chalk-muted">
        The output is a working document, not a static report. I revisit and update
        keyword strategies as campaigns evolve, rankings shift, and search behaviour
        changes, because the best SEO is always adapting.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 4. Relevant result (light) ──────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="sp-result section-light">
    <div class="container sp-result-inner reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow dark-eyebrow">Proven Results</p>
      <blockquote class="sp-quote">
        <p class="sp-quote-metric">Top 3 core product keywords · +99.5% revenue</p>
        <p class="sp-quote-context">
          For Number 1 Plates, a comprehensive keyword strategy backed by competitor
          and persona research mapped high-intent purchase terms across their product
          range. Combined with technical and on-page work, it drove their core product
          keywords into the top three and nearly doubled revenue.
        </p>
        <footer class="sp-quote-credit">— Number 1 Plates (Automotive eCommerce · UK)</footer>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 5. Related Services ─────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="related-services section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Related Services</p>
      <div class="related-grid">
        <a href="/on-page-seo/" class="related-card">
          <strong>On-Page SEO</strong>
          <span>Put your keyword research into action — optimise titles, content and structure.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/technical-seo/" class="related-card">
          <strong>Technical SEO</strong>
          <span>Ensure your site can be crawled and indexed so your keywords can rank.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/seo-strategy/" class="related-card">
          <strong>SEO Strategy</strong>
          <span>Turn keyword insights into a full-funnel SEO roadmap for your business.</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── 6. Contact CTA ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <ContactForm />

</ServicePage>

<style>
  .section-dark  { background-color: var(--ink);  color: var(--chalk); }
  .section-light { background-color: var(--chalk); color: var(--ink); }

  .container {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: clamp(1.25rem, 5vw, 2rem);
  }

  .sp-hero { padding: 5rem 0 4rem; }
  .sp-hero-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .eyebrow {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .dark-eyebrow { color: var(--accent); }

  .sp-h1 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--chalk);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .sp-intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(248, 247, 242, 0.75);
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    background-color: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
    align-self: flex-start;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover { background-color: var(--accent-dk); }

  .sp-content { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .sp-content-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .sp-h2 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .sp-h2.chalk { color: var(--chalk); }

  .sp-h3 {
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .sp-content p, .sp-content-inner p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.8);
  }

  .sp-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .sp-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.8);
  }
  .sp-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .sp-why { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .sp-why-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }
  .chalk { color: var(--chalk); }
  .chalk-muted {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(248, 247, 242, 0.75);
  }

  .sp-result { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .sp-result-inner { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .sp-quote {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    background-color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.04);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  .sp-quote-metric {
    font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .sp-quote-context {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(10, 10, 15, 0.75);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .sp-quote-credit {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .reveal {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(24px);
    transition: opacity 0.55s ease, transform 0.55s ease;
  }
  .reveal.visible {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: none;
  }

  /* ── Related services ──────────────────────────────────────── */
  .related-services { padding: 3rem 0; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07); }
  .related-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 640px) { .related-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); } }
  .related-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.375rem;
    padding: 1.125rem 1.25rem;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
  }
  .related-card:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.07); border-color: rgba(255,104,38,0.4); }
  .related-card strong { font-size: 0.9375rem; color: #F8F7F2; font-weight: 600; }
  .related-card span { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: rgba(248,247,242,0.5); line-height: 1.55; }
</style>

<script>
  const revealEls = document.querySelectorAll('.reveal');
  const io = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => entries.forEach(e => { if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('visible'); io.unobserve(e.target); } }),
    { threshold: 0.12 }
  );
  revealEls.forEach(el => io.observe(el));
</script>
